cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CY

This paper focuses on the design and evaluation of a tool called Transfer Tutor that supports learning transfer between programming languages. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. 

Firstly, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a likely category as the paper discusses the usability and effectiveness of Transfer Tutor as a tool for supporting learning transfer. 

Secondly, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper deals with the translation of code explanations from one programming language to another. 

Thirdly, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper applies the theory of learning transfer to teach a new programming language. 

Fourthly, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the challenges of learning a new programming language and proposes a tool to support this process. 

Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of programming language expertise on programmers and proposes a tool to support their learning.
